      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety instructions before operating.</strong> Failure to follow these instructions may result in serious injury, electric shock, or damage to the tool.
      </div>

      <h3>Required Personal Protective Equipment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Safety glasses or face shield</li>
        <li>Respirator or dust mask</li>
        <li>Closed-toe footwear</li>
        <li>Heavy canvas or leather apron (recommended for carving)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Critical Safety Rules</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Always wear proper eye and face protection when operating the tool.</li>
        <li>Secure workpieces in a vise or work-holding device &mdash; never hold by hand.</li>
        <li>Do not wear loose clothing, jewelry, or neckties. Tie back long hair.</li>
        <li>Secure the motor to a motor hanger or work surface to prevent it from jumping at startup.</li>
        <li>Never use an accessory with a speed rating lower than 15,000 RPM (TX Series).</li>
        <li>Never use or continue to use any accessory that appears damaged, loose, vibrating, or out of balance.</li>
        <li>Do not stall the motor by jamming or applying excessive pressure.</li>
        <li>Never operate the motor with the outer sheath removed from the flexible shaft.</li>
        <li>Always disconnect the power cord before servicing or removing the shaft/sheath.</li>
        <li>Never operate during a perceptible power decrease.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Speed control restriction:</strong> Never modify the shielded plug on the TX motor cord to plug it into a non-TX speed control or AC wall outlet. Use only TXR, SXR, or EMX speed controls with Series TX motors. Serious motor damage will result from using other controls or plugging the motor directly into an AC outlet.
      </div>

      <h3>Grounding</h3>
      <p>This tool must be grounded while in use. It is equipped with a 3-conductor cord and 3-prong grounding plug. The green (or green and yellow) conductor is the grounding wire &mdash; never connect it to a live terminal. Use only 3-wire extension cords with matching 3-prong plugs. Some jurisdictions prohibit 3-to-2-prong adapters.</p>

