      <h3>Attaching Accessories</h3>

      <h4>Collet-Type Handpieces (H.8, H.8D, H.25, H.28, H.43T, H.44T)</h4>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/foredom-tx/p08_00.png" alt="Diagram of collet handpiece showing pilot hole, collet, and chuck nut assembly" />
        <figcaption>Collet handpiece assembly detail</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Use the correct shank size collet &mdash; the shank must fit snugly inside the collet.</li>
        <li>Insert the pin into the pilot hole through the spindle hole (turn spindle to align).</li>
        <li>Loosen the chuck nut with the wrench provided.</li>
        <li>Insert the accessory shank as far as possible into the collet.</li>
        <li>Tighten the chuck nut with the wrench, keeping the pin in the pilot hole.</li>
        <li>Test for a secure hold by pulling on the accessory. Remove the pin.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Never tighten an empty collet.</strong> Tightening without an accessory inserted, or using an incorrectly sized shank, may damage the collet.
      </div>

      <h4>Chuck-Type Handpiece (H.30)</h4>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/foredom-tx/p08_01.png" alt="Diagram of H.30 chuck handpiece with chuck key" />
        <figcaption>H.30 chuck handpiece</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Open chuck jaws with the key provided.</li>
        <li>Insert the accessory shank fully into the chuck.</li>
        <li>Tighten jaws with the chuck key until the accessory is secure and centered.</li>
        <li>If the accessory does not run true, reopen jaws, rotate the accessory, and retighten.</li>
      </ol>

      <h4>Quick-Change Handpieces (H.10, H.18, H.20)</h4>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/foredom-tx/p08_02.png" alt="Diagram of quick-change handpiece lever mechanisms" />
        <figcaption>Quick-change handpiece lever operation</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>H.10/H.10D:</strong> Turn lever 180&deg; clockwise toward the back, insert or change accessory (2.35 mm shank), turn lever 180&deg; forward counterclockwise. Ensure lever locks fully forward.</li>
        <li><strong>H.18/H.18D:</strong> Push the spring-loaded side lever down to open the collet and release/insert the accessory. Never push the lever down while rotating.</li>
        <li><strong>H.20/H.20D:</strong> Turn lever 90&deg; left or right to open the collet, change accessory, and return lever to the position parallel to the handpiece.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Keep an accessory in quick-change handpieces at all times</strong> (during both operation and storage) to prevent collet and handpiece damage.
      </div>

