      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Motor does not start</td>
            <td>Speed control in &ldquo;off&rdquo; position; cord not connected</td>
            <td>Verify all connections and engage control</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Motor runs but handpiece does not spin</td>
            <td>Shaft key tip not aligned in handpiece keyway</td>
            <td>Remove handpiece and re-attach using the half-speed alignment method (see Assembly)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Excessive vibration or noise</td>
            <td>Shaft bent too tightly; worn shaft; improper shaft adjustment</td>
            <td>Maintain 4&Prime; minimum bend radius; check shaft extension is 3/4&Prime;; replace shaft if worn</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Shaft overheating</td>
            <td>Insufficient lubrication; too-tight bend angle</td>
            <td>Clean and re-lubricate shaft; reduce bend angle</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Motor very hot</td>
            <td>Prolonged use; restricted airflow</td>
            <td>Normal up to 100&deg;F + ambient; ensure motor is not enclosed</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Loss of speed or power</td>
            <td>Worn motor brushes; dust buildup</td>
            <td>Inspect brushes (replace at 1/4&Prime;); clean motor with compressed air</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Grease seeping from handpiece end</td>
            <td>Too much grease applied to shaft</td>
            <td>Apply less grease near handpiece end; run motor 10 min to distribute before attaching handpiece</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Fuse blows on EMX dial control</td>
            <td>Motor overloaded</td>
            <td>Reduce load; replace fuse (located below power cord receptacle on control)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Motor damage</td>
            <td>Wrong speed control used; motor plugged directly into wall outlet</td>
            <td>Use only TXR, SXR, or EMX controls &mdash; never modify the shielded plug</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Storage and Repair</h2>
      <p>Store in a dry, clean, dust-free area out of the reach of children.</p>
